{"id":"2007.04284","submitter":"Julien Sabin","authors":"Rupert L. Frank and Julien Sabin","title":"Sharp Weyl laws with singular potentials","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Pure Appl. Analysis 5 (2023) 85-144","doi":"10.2140/paa.2023.5.85","report-no":null,"categories":"math-ph math.AP math.MP math.SP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We consider the Laplace--Beltrami operator on a three-dimensional Riemannian\nmanifold perturbed by a potential from the Kato class and study whether various\nforms of Weyl's law remain valid under this perturbation. We show that a\npointwise Weyl law holds, modified by an additional term, for any Kato class\npotential with the standard sharp remainder term. The additional term is always\nof lower order than the leading term, but it may or may not be of lower order\nthan the sharp remainder term. In particular, we provide examples of singular\npotentials for which this additional term violates the sharp pointwise Weyl law\nof the standard Laplace-Beltrami operator. For the proof we extend the method\nof Avakumovi\\'c to the case of Schr\\\"odinger operators with singular\npotentials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Jul 2020 17:33:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-26"}
